SIMPLE: embellishment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embellishment
<hw>Em*bel"lish*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>embellissement</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of adorning,
or the state of being adorned; adornment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the selection of their ground, as well as in the
<qex>embellishment</qex> of it.</q> <rj><qau>Prescott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which adds beauty or elegance; ornament;
decoration; <as>as, pictorial <ex>embellishments</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The graces and <qex>embellishments</qex> of the exterior man.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ember</ent>⟦br⟧
